DataElement.preferredDefinition: Any record of a medical imaging event whether physical or electronic.:In image processing, a piece of information which is relevant for solving the computational task related to a certain application, either specific structures in the image itself (e.g., simple structures such as points or edges to more complex structures such as objects) or the result of a general neighborhood operation (feature extractor or feature detector) applied to the image.:A group of things of the same kind that belong together and are so used._Occurring first in time or sequence; original; of greatest rank or importance or value.:Where something is available or from where it originates.:Any record of an imaging event whether physical or electronic._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is a long integer (64-bit two's complement).
